# Keep secrets and runtime data OUT of the image build context. The Dockerfile
# does `COPY . .`, so anything not excluded here is baked into image layers —
# a `docker save`/`docker push` of the tag would leak it, and old layers keep
# old secrets even after rotation. Runtime gets these another way: env vars via
# compose env_file, certs via the ./certs bind mount, data via named volumes.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
certs/
keys/
storage/
logs/
uploads/
temp/
tmp/
# Stray keys/certs/DBs/logs anywhere in the tree (defense-in-depth:
# the certs/ and keys/ dirs above are already excluded; the **/ prefix catches a loose file
# in ANY subdirectory (bare patterns only match at the context root),
# a working checkout might contain, since the Dockerfile does `COPY . .`).
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/*.crt
**/*.cert
**/*.db
**/*.sqlite3
**/*.log

# Build hygiene (never needed inside the image)
tests/
CLAUDE.md
# TypeScript sources / JS build tooling: the served crypto is the hand-maintained
# static/js/*.js; no .ts is compiled at build, so none of this belongs in the image.
**/*.ts
tsconfig.json
package.json
package-lock.json
node_modules/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.py[cod]
**/.pytest_cache/
# Local virtualenvs (routinely created to run tests/) + dev/build/IDE artifacts
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/
.coverage
htmlcov/
dist/
build/
.vscode/
.idea/
**/*.backup
**/*.bak
**/*.old
**/*.swp
**/*.swo
**/*~
setup_state.json
setup.lock
# NB: .dockerignore patterns are filepath.Match-style, NOT gitignore-style — a bare
# pattern matches at the context root only, so the deploy/ copies need their own line.
docker-compose*.yml
deploy/docker-compose*.yml
# Host-side setup / management tooling (run on the host to build/start/operate the stack) — not
# part of the runtime image. (The root docker-compose*.yml shims are already excluded above.)
setup-secure.sh
setup-secure.ps1
dockvault.py
.dockerignore
.gitignore
# Keep VCS metadata out of the shipped public image (a submodule .git is just a 58-byte gitdir
# pointer, but it still leaks the internal submodule/monorepo path layout).
.git
.git/
# CI / repo config (Dependabot etc.) — not part of the runtime image.
.github/
